[The classic _Salmonella_ serovar of pigs is _choleraesuis_, but many
others are common and may be more common. These serovars include
_Typhimurium_ var. Copenhagen, Derby, Heidelberg and
Infantis. Ciprofloxacin resistance is becoming more common in these
strains. - Mod.LL]
